{
  "id": "nce2-l38",
  "title": "Lesson 38: Everything Except the Weather",
  "audio": "/audio/nce2/38ÔºçEverything Except the Weather.mp3",
  "image": "/images/coming-soon.png",
  "segments": [
    {
      "id": "intro_1",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "Why did Harrison sell his house so quickly?",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 10.98,
      "endTime": 16.5
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_2",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "My old friend, Harrison, had lived in",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 16.51,
      "endTime": 19.99
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_3",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "the Mediterranean for many years",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 20,
      "endTime": 22.64
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_4",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "before he returned to England.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 22.65,
      "endTime": 25.96
    },
    {
      "id": "s1",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "He had often dreamed of retiring in England",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 25.97,
      "endTime": 29.88
    },
    {
      "id": "s2",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "and had planned to settle down in the country.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 29.89,
      "endTime": 33.6
    },
    {
      "id": "s3",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "He had no sooner returned than he bought",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 33.61,
      "endTime": 37.37
    },
    {
      "id": "s4",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "a house and went to live there.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 37.38,
      "endTime": 40.04
    },
    {
      "id": "s5",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Almost immediately he began to complain",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 40.05,
      "endTime": 43.61
    },
    {
      "id": "s6",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "about the weather,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 43.62,
      "endTime": 45.61
    },
    {
      "id": "s7",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "for even though it was still summer,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 45.62,
      "endTime": 49.19
    },
    {
      "id": "s8",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "it rained continually and it was often bitterly cold.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 49.2,
      "endTime": 54.83
    },
    {
      "id": "s9",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "After so many years of sunshine,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 54.84,
      "endTime": 57.83
    },
    {
      "id": "s10",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "Harrison got a shock.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 57.84,
      "endTime": 60.46
    },
    {
      "id": "s11",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "He acted as if he had never lived in England before.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 60.47,
      "endTime": 65.59
    },
    {
      "id": "s12",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "In the end, it was more than he could bear.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 65.6,
      "endTime": 69.78
    },
    {
      "id": "s13",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "He had hardly had time to settle down",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 69.79,
      "endTime": 73.03
    },
    {
      "id": "s14",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "when he sold the house and left the country.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 73.04,
      "endTime": 77.2
    },
    {
      "id": "s15",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "The dream he had had for so many years ended there.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 77.21,
      "endTime": 82.78
    },
    {
      "id": "s16",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "Harrison had thought of everything except the weather.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 82.79,
      "endTime": 87.79
    }
  ]
}